Important terms and concepts are listed here.  
 
API: An application program interface (API) is code that allows two software programs to communicate with each other 
  
SDD: System Design Document 
 
SYSTEM: Any interactions performed by the application are considered to be performed by the system. 
  
MSSQL: Short for Microsoft SQL Server. It is a relational web hosting database that is used to store web site information. 
  
MVC: The Model-View-Controller (MVC) architectural pattern separates an application into three main components:
the model, the view, and the controller. 
 
MODEL: A schematic description of a system that accounts for its known or inferred properties. 
 
VIEW: A visual representation of a model which might. 
